Recreation - Pool Attendant Al Ghurair Arjaan by Rotana
We are currently looking for young,
dynamic,
self motivated Recreation professionals who want to move their careers forward.
As a Pool Attendant you are responsible to ensure that all pool area responsibilities are carried out in an efficient and timely manner,
whereby your role will include key responsibilities such as:
•Ensure swimming pools (main and kids pool) are clean
•Constantly monitor swimming pool activities
•Ensure no fighting occurs in the swimming pool area
•Monitor people’s actions whether if they are causing danger to others
•Assist anybody who is in any difficulty in and around the pool area
•Regularly check the temperature of the pool and report to the Superiors
•Ensure any lost property found is handed as per company guidelines
•Report any guest complaints to your Superiors immediately
•Have full knowledge of club’s facilities,
timings,
promotions and prices.
Skills
Education,
Qualifications & Experiences
You should ideally have a diploma or vocational training in the sports / leisure field with preferable previous work experiences within a hotel. Physically fit and able to work long hours in an outside environment are essentials. Good command of English and good interpersonal abilities are an advantage.
Knowledge & Competencies
The ideal candidate will be customer driven with good guest service skills and the ability to handle complaints. You are a positive,
smiley individual with a sportive,
outgoing and approachable character. You will work well under pressure in a fast paced environment and be a great team player,
who thrives in working with a multi-cultural team and guests alike,
while possessing following additional competencies:
Understanding the job
Teamwork
Teamwork
Taking Responsibility
Recognising Differences
Adaptability
Customer Focus
